<div id="review_430747953" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/430747953" />
    <a title="Jen (LOHF/Book Den) " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1384646-jen-lohf-book-den"><img alt="Jen (LOHF/Book Den) " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1571332684p2/1384646.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/430747953?book_show_action=true">Oct 09, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jen (LOHF/Book Den) " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jen (LOHF/Book Den) " href="/user/show/1384646-jen-lohf-book-den">Jen (LOHF/Book Den) </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1384646-jen-lohf-book-den?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer430747953" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11692017212683376338">As much as I love reading a great horror novel, I love watching horror movies as well. Now that I have young children, I don&apos;t get to watch many (any!) horror flicks. Michael West&apos;s Harmony, Indiana books are a great combination of both worlds. The fun and the scares are much like watching a horror movie. The movie references scattered throughout are an added bonus as well.<br/><br/>Spook House is a great book to read this time of year. The Halloween tie-in was more subtle than I expected; you could defin</span>
  <span id="freeText11692017212683376338" style="display:none">As much as I love reading a great horror novel, I love watching horror movies as well. Now that I have young children, I don't get to watch many (any!) horror flicks. Michael West's Harmony, Indiana books are a great combination of both worlds. The fun and the scares are much like watching a horror movie. The movie references scattered throughout are an added bonus as well.<br /><br />Spook House is a great book to read this time of year. The Halloween tie-in was more subtle than I expected; you could definitely curl up with this one any time of the season.<br /><br />If you haven't read anything by Michael West, Spook House is a perfect place to start. His Harmony, Indiana books are stand alone and entertaining in any order you choose to read them. Although, after reading Spook House, you will likely have a strong desire to pick up <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/18160656.The_Wide_Game__Harmony__Indiana___1_" title="The Wide Game (Harmony, Indiana, #1) by Michael West" rel="nofollow noopener">The Wide Game</a> next.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11692017212683376338" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

